	"bag of holding (ccc-bmg-moon1-3)" : {
		name : "Bag of Holding (CCC-BMG-MOON1-3)",
		source : [["AL","CCC"]],
		rarity : "uncommon",
		description : "This black velvet bag is embroidered in gold with a dwarven rune. It's 2 ft sq, 4 ft deep, & always weighs 5 lb. The bag holds 500 lb & 64 cu ft. Utilize to retrieve item. If overloaded, pierced, or torn, it's destroyed & contents go to the Astral plane. Turn inside out to empty bag. Has 10 min of air. One-way gate to Astral Plane opens if put in extradimensional space from similar item; all in 10 ft sucked in.",
		descriptionLong : "This black velvet bag is adorned with a dwarven rune embroidered on the outside in gold thread. The bag is 2 ft sq, 4 ft deep, & 5 lb regardless of contents. It holds up to 500 lbs & 64 cu ft in volume. Retrieving an item requires the Utilize action. If overloaded, pierced, or torn, the bag is destroyed, leaving its contents in the Astral plane. If turned inside out, its contents spill forth unharmed. Creatures inside the bag can breathe for 10 min divided by number of creatures (minimum 1). Placing the bag in another extradimensional space from item destroys both & opens a one-way gate to the Astral Plane that sucks all within 10 ft inside before closing.",
		descriptionFull : "This black velvet bag is adorned with a dwarven rune embroidered on the outside in gold thread.\n   This bag has an interior space considerably larger than its outside dimensions, roughly 2 feet square and 4 feet deep on the inside. The bag can hold up to 500 pounds, not exceeding a volume of 64 cubic feet. The bag weighs 5 pounds, regardless of its contents. Retrieving an item from the bag requires a Utilize action.\n   If the bag is overloaded, pierced, or torn, it is destroyed, and its contents are scattered in the Astral Plane. If the bag is turned inside out, its contents spill forth unharmed, but the bag must be put right before it can be used again. The bag holds enough air for 10 minutes of breathing, divided by the number of breathing creatures inside.\n   Placing a Bag of Holding inside an extradimensional space created by a Heward's Handy Haversack, Portable Hole, or similar item instantly destroys both items and opens a gate to the Astral Plane. The gate originates where the one item was placed inside the other. Any creature within a 10-foot-radius Sphere centered on the gate is sucked through it to a random location on the Astral Plane. The gate then closes. The gate is one-way and can't be reopened.",
		weight : 5,
		action : [["action", "Bag of Holding (retrieve item)"]]
	},
