	"fish suit: d'cannith (ddal0-15)" : {
		name : "D'Cannith Fish Suit (DDAL0-15)",
		source : [["AL","SJ-DC"]],
		rarity : "very rare",
		description : "This bulky suit lets me breathe without air and makes me immune to gas. It gives me a swimming speed underwater & a flying speed in zero gravity. The suit is highly experimental. If I take 20+ dmg, I roll a mishap that lasts until it's repaired (DC 15). Mishaps: 1. 3d6 fire at start of turn (Int)/2-4. Can only move in straight line. Fails Dex d20 rolls (Int)./5-7. Half speed (Dex)/8-10. Nothing/11-13. Blinded (Int)/14-16. Mishap on 10+ dmg (Dex)/17-19. Stops functioning (20 Dex)/Suit explodes. DC 20 Con save: 6d10 force and prone (save 1/2 only).",
		descriptionLong : "This bulky suit lets me breathe without air and makes me immune to gas. It gives me a swimming speed underwater & a flying speed in zero gravity, both equal my walking speed. The suit is highly experimental. If I take 20+ dmg, I roll a mishap that lasts until it's repaired. Mishaps: 1. Take 3d6 fire at start of turn (DC 15 Int)/2-4. Can only move in straight line. Fails Dex chks and saves (DC 15 Int)./5-7. Half speed (DC 15 Dex)/8-10. Nothing happens/11-13. Blinded (DC 15 Int)/14-16. Mishap occurs on 10+ dmg (DC 15 Dex)/17-19. Suit stops functioning (DC 20 Dex)/Suit explodes and is destroyed. DC 20 Con save vs 6d10 force and prone (save 1/2 only).",
		descriptionFull : "This bulky suit, which fully encases your head and body, takes 1 minute to don or doff. While worn, it enables you to breathe in an airless environment and renders you immune to the harmful effects of any gas that surrounds you. The suit also grants you a swimming speed equal to your walking speed while underwater, or a flying speed equal to your walking speed in an environment with no gravity.\n   " + toUni("Mishaps") + ". The suit is highly experimental and mostly based on \"theory\", so is prone to mishaps when damaged. If you take 20 more damage while wearing a D'Cannith Fish Suit, roll on the mishap chart below. If a mishap has a repair DC, the mishap can be ended by making repairs to the suit. The creature must be within reach of the damaged area in need of repair, and the creature must have the right tools for the job (smith's tools or tinker's tools, for example). A creature can use its action to make an ability check based on the nature of the mishap (see the Mishaps table). The creature adds its proficiency bronus to the check if it's proficient with the tools used to make the repairs. A successful check ends the mishap. A mishap with no repair DC can't be repaired." + toUni("Mishaps") + ". \n\n" + toUni("d20    Mishaps\tRepair DC") + "\n  1\tOxygen Ignition. Fire erupts from the air systems and engulfs the suit. A creature that starts its turn while wearing the suit takes 10 (3d6) fire damage until this mishap ends.\t15(Int)\n  2-4\tLocked Movement. The creature wearing the suit can move in a straight line only. It automatically fails Dexterity checks and Dexterity saving throws until this mishap ends.\t15(Int)\n  5-7\tHydraulic Failure. The creature wearing the suit has their movement reduced by half until this mishap ends.\t15(Dex)\n  8-10\tNo mishap occurs.\tNone\n  11-13\tBlinding Smoke. The suit fills with smoke and the creature wearing it is blinded until this mishap ends.\t15(Int)\n  14-16\tFraying. The damage you can take before needing to roll a mishap is reduced by 10 until this mishap ends.\t15(Dex)\n  17-19\tSuit Rupture. The suit's features stop functioning until this mishap ends.\t20(Dex)\n  20\tTotal Catastrophic Failure. The suit combusts and explodes. A creature wearing it must make a DC 20 Constitution saving throw, taking 6d10 force damage and being knocked prone on a failed save, or taking half as much damage and not being knocked prone on a successful one. The suit is then permanently destroyed.\t\n\n",
		savetxt : { immune : ["surrounding gas"] },
		speed : { swim : { spd : "walk", enc : "walk" } }, // flying speed is more situational, so not added to the listing
	},
