		source : [["AL","CCC"]],
		rarity : "rare",
		description : "This black iron brazier is warm to the touch. Painted red & orange flames cover its surface around a symbol of the Cult of Eternal Flame. When on my person, I can speak Ignan. Once per dawn while a fire burns in the brazier, I can summon a fire elemental as a Magic action. It understands my languages, obeys my commands and acts directly after me. It disappears after 1 hr, at 0 HP or with a bonus action.",
		descriptionFull : "This item is warm to the touch and it appears to be crafted from black iron. Sigils of flames cover its surface surrounding a symbol of the Cult of Eternal Flame painted in orange and red. While this brazier is on a bearer's person, that person can speak and understand Ignan.\n   While you are within 5 feet of this brazier, you can take a Magic action to summon a Fire Elemental. The elemental appears in an unoccupied space as close to the brazier as possible, understands your languages, obeys your commands, and takes its turn immediately after you on your Initiative count. The elemental disappears after 1 hour, when it dies, or when you dismiss it as a Bonus Action. The brazier can't be used this way again until the next dawn.",
