		description : "This large finely glazed ceramic bowl is painted with depictions of malevolent arson. Old cracks were filled with gold, creating a beautiful spiderweb of art. When used, thick heavily obscuring acrid smoke fills a 10-ft radius around the bowl. Once per dawn while a fire burns, I can summon a fire elemental as a Magic action. It understands my languages, obeys my commands and acts directly after me. It disappears after 1 hr, at 0 HP or with a bonus action.",
		descriptionFull : "This large bowl is made of finely glazed ceramic painted with various depictions of malevolent arson. Old cracks have been filled in with gold, creating an impeccably beautiful spiderweb of contrasting art. When used, thick, acrid smoke fills a 10-foot-radius sphere around the bowl, heavily obscuring vision.\n   While you are within 5 feet of this brazier, you can take a Magic action to summon a Fire Elemental. The elemental appears in an unoccupied space as close to the brazier as possible, understands your languages, obeys your commands, and takes its turn immediately after you on your Initiative count. The elemental disappears after 1 hour, when it dies, or when you dismiss it as a Bonus Action. The brazier can't be used this way again until the next dawn.",
