		source : [["AL","SJ-DC"]],
		description : "Smoke lingers around me when exhaled from this delicate wooden pipe with a river stone bowl. After 10 min once per dawn, that smoke can form moving shapes. They realistically reenact my most impressive and heroic deeds for 5 min, after which the smoke dissipates. The last memory is always the moment when I convinced Aneerya not to kill the Tutor, followed by her and her adopted child waving. The pipe also warns me, giving +2 Initiative if not Incapacitated.",
		descriptionFull : "This long, delicate wooden pipe features a bowl made from smooth river stone. When the pipe is lit, smoke exhaled from it does not dissipate, instead lingering around the bearer. After 10 minutes, the smoke forms moving shapes that reenact the bearer's most impressive and heroic achievements for 5 minutes. When this realistic performance is complete, the smoke dissipates. The pipe can't be used this way again until the next dawn.\n   When lit, these pipes depict the moment when the characters convinced Aneerya not to kill the Tutor as their final memory each time, followed by the image of her and her adopted child waving at them.\n   " + toUni("Guardian") + ". The item warns you, granting a +2 bonus to your Initiative rolls if you don't have the Incapacitated condition.",
