		source : [["AL","WBW-DC"]],
		attunement : true,
		description : "This wooden figure is 4-in tall, carved & painted in my likeness. If I genuinely tried to help Salvation, it's beautifully & accurately painted with 11 points of articulation. If I didn't try to help, the figure is poorly painted with 5 points of articulation. During a short rest, I can teach it up to 6 phrases, up to 6 words each, & set observable conditions as triggers. Conditions must happen within 5 ft. The doll can only learn 6 phrases, which are lost when I unattune.",
		descriptionFull : "This wooden figure is 4 inches tall, and carved and painted to resemble the characters. If the characters made a genuine attempt to help Salvation, the figure is beautifully and accurately painted with 11 points of articulation. If the characters made no attempt to help Salvation, the figure is poorly painted with 5 points of articulation.\n   While this doll is within 5 feet of you, you can spend a Short Rest telling it to say up to six phrases, none of which can be more than six words long, and set a condition under which the doll speaks each phrase. You can also replace old phrases with new ones. Whatever the condition, it must occur within 5 feet of the doll to make it speak. For example, whenever someone picks up the doll, it might say, “I want a piece of candy.” The doll's phrases are lost when your Attunement to the doll ends."
