		source : [["AL","CCC"]],
		rarity : "uncommon",
		description : "At first glance, this platinum ring is engraved with golden leaves. Closer inspection shows a story of an elven man & human woman falling in love. Two words are engraved on the inside, but the text is too old to understand. They may be names of the first half elf's parents or notes of the lovebirds' song. I reduce Cold dmg taken by 2d8. I'm also unharmed by temperatures below 0\u00B0F along with everything I wear & carry.",
		descriptionFull : "At first glance, this platinum ring has golden leaves engraved onto it. Upon closer inspection, though, you notice it depicts a story of an elven man and human woman falling in love. Two elven words are engraved on the inside of the ring, likely the couples' names, but the text is too ancient for anyone to understand. One might wonder whether these are the names of the parents of the first half elf, or just the notes of two lovebirds' song. The real question is where did Bert find this ring in the first place!\n   If you take Cold damage while wearing this ring, the ring reduces the damage you take by 2d8.\n   In addition, while wearing this ring, you and everything you wear and carry are unharmed by temperatures of 0 degrees Fahrenheit or lower.",
