	"ioun stone - reserve (ccc-bmg-48 hill3-3)" : {
		name: "Ioun Stone - Reserve (CCC-BMG-48 HILL3-3)",
		source : [["AL","CCC"]],
		rarity : "rare",
		attunement : true,
		description : "This deep violet, almost indigo, translucent prism has a noticeable chunk broken off 1 corner. While orbiting my head, the stone emits a low buzzing, like an insect, which only I can hear. Magic action to orbit at 1d3 ft. Utilize to stow. 3 lvls of spells can be stored in it and cast to free space using original caster's ability.",
		descriptionLong : "This deep violet, almost indigo, translucent prism has a noticeable chunk broken off 1 corner. As a Magic action, I can make it orbit my head at 1d3 ft. Utilize to retrieve it. While orbiting my head, the stone emits a low buzzing, like an insect, which only I can hear. It can store 3 (spell slot) levels worth of spells. By touching it, one can cast a 1-3 level spell into it. I can cast any spell stored in it as if casting it myself, but using the original caster's spellcasting ability. It contains lighting bolt when found.",
		descriptionFull : "An Ioun stone is named after Ioun, a god of knowledge and prophecy revered on some worlds. Many types of Ioun stone exist, each type a distinct combination of shape and color.\n   When you use a Magic action to toss one of these stones into the air, the stone orbits your head at a distance of 1d3 feet and confers a benefit to you. You can use a Utilize action to seize and stow the stone, ending its effect.\n   It is considered to be an object that is being worn while it orbits your head.\n   This vibrant purple prism stores spells cast into it, holding them until you use them. The stone can store up to 4 levels of spells at a time. When found, it contains 1d4 levels of stored spells chosen by the DM.\n   Any creature can cast a spell of level 1 through 4 into the stone by touching it as the spell is cast. The spell has no effect, other than to be stored in the stone. If the stone can't hold the spell, the spell is expended without effect. The level of the slot used to cast the spell determines how much space it uses.\n   While this stone orbits your head, you can cast any spell stored in it. The spell uses the slot level, spell save DC, spell attack bonus, and spellcasting ability of the original caster but is otherwise treated as if you cast the spell. The spell cast from the stone is no longer stored in it, freeing up space.\n   This deep violet, almost indigo, translucent prism has a noticeable chunk broken off of one corner. When found, it contains the spell lightning bolt. While orbiting the owner's head, the stone emits a low buzzing, like an insect, which is only perceptible to the owner.",
		},
	"ioun stone - reserve (ccc-ylra1-1)" : {
		name: "Ioun Stone - Reserve (CCC-YLRA1-1)",
		source : [["AL","CCC"]],
		rarity : "rare",
		attunement : true,
		description : "This purple gem, the Peacemaker's Coin, has a face carved on each side: an elf woman with ruby-tinted hair & a dwarf with the symbol of Clangeddin Silverbeard. In darkness, ghostly shapes trail from it. I get +1 to Cha (Persuasion) chks to resolve conflict. Magic action to orbit at 1d3 ft. Utilize to stow. The gem holds 3 lvls of spells. When casting into it, the caster hears male & female voices arguing. When I cast a spell from it, I hear the voices chant in unison.",
		descriptionLong : "This purple gem is cut like a coin, with a face on each side. One is an elf woman with long ruby-tinted hair, and the other is an older dwarf in a helm with the symbol of Clangeddin Silverbeard. In darkness, I see ghostly shapes trailing after the jewel as it moves. While attuned I gain +1 on Charisma (Persuasion) checks to resolve conflict or calm emotions. The stone was known as the Peacemaker's Coin in the dwarf kingdom of Roldilar, where it belonged to the human mage Beldossan the Short. As Magic action, I can make it orbit my head at 1d3 ft. Utilize to retrieve it. It can store 3 (spell slot) levels worth of spells. By touching it, one can cast a 1-3 level spell into it. The caster hears male and female voices arguing. I can cast any stored spell using the original caster's spellcasting ability. When I do, I hear the same voices chanting in unison.",
		descriptionFull : "An Ioun stone is named after Ioun, a god of knowledge and prophecy revered on some worlds. Many types of Ioun stone exist, each type a distinct combination of shape and color.\n   When you use a Magic action to toss one of these stones into the air, the stone orbits your head at a distance of 1d3 feet and confers a benefit to you. You can use a Utilize action to seize and stow the stone, ending its effect.\n   It is considered to be an object that is being worn while it orbits your head.\n   This vibrant purple prism stores spells cast into it, holding them until you use them. The stone can store up to 4 levels of spells at a time. When found, it contains 1d4 levels of stored spells chosen by the DM.\n   Any creature can cast a spell of level 1 through 4 into the stone by touching it as the spell is cast. The spell has no effect, other than to be stored in the stone. If the stone can't hold the spell, the spell is expended without effect. The level of the slot used to cast the spell determines how much space it uses.\n   While this stone orbits your head, you can cast any spell stored in it. The spell uses the slot level, spell save DC, spell attack bonus, and spellcasting ability of the original caster but is otherwise treated as if you cast the spell. The spell cast from the stone is no longer stored in it, freeing up space.\n   Rather than appearing as a prism like a normal ioun stone of its type, however, this purple gem is cut like a coin, with a face on each side. One is an elf woman whose long hair has a ruby tint, and the other is an older dwarf in a helm bearing the symbol of the dwarf god Clangeddin Silverbeard. In darkness, one can see ghostly shapes trailing after the coin-like jewel as it moves. When a spell is cast into the stone, the caster hears a male and female voice arguing. When a spell is unleashed from it, the same voices are heard chanting in unison by the user. Anyone attuned to this item receives to +1 bonus on Charisma (Persuasion) checks to resolve conflict or calm emotions. Research indicates this item was known as the Peacemaker's Coin in the old dwarf kingdom of Roldilar, where it belonged to the human mage and dwarf ally Beldossan the Short.",
		},
